==English==

===Etymology===

Surface: French ''sur'' + French ''face''     runoff: run + off

===Noun===
'''Surface runoff'''  (''plural:'' '''Surface runoff''')
 
:Overland flow of excess water that cannot be absorbed by the ground as [[infiltration]].

===Example usage===

:''When there is very heavy rainfall on California hillsides, there is almost always ensuing surface runoff''

